column5: I am planning a fishing trip to the West Arm early July. Need some advise as I have never been there before. Where can I launch my 16' aluminum boat and park for 3 days? I am planning to camp out, are there crown land sites or park sites available? I usually fish for Bass, Walleye and Pike, any recommended spots to fish?  Thanks for your reply
The 'west arm' encompasses a very large area, so you may have to be a little more specific
West side of Hwy 64. May also go to the east side (West Bay).
Don't forget there's musky in them dar waters

Maybe try Memquisit Lodge, their just east of 64 and may let you park for the 3 days.  Plenty of empty islands up in West Bay too and I've often seen tents on them.  https://www.google.ca/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=1&cad=rja&uact=8&sqi=2&ved=0CCIQFjAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.memquisitlodge.net%2F&ei=qg2SU_jVLYeOyATMq4DQAQ&usg=AFQjCNGSBtQDrB8MkFPhKPcQfp05MIyJ4w&bvm=bv.68445247,d.aWw
That one will not fit into my frying pan!

Mmmmmm deep fried Muskie served with a side of pre-spawn bass, and a mixed salad including a sturgeon drizzled in beluga caviar  mmmmm  Check out welcome lodge. They should be able to accommodate your request.   G
there is a lauch at sucker creek on 64,you could probably leave your vehicle there ,there is some parking
I went to west arm lodge last year. I stayed in one of their cottages but as far as I know you can camp out there too. Owners are real nice friendly people.
